content: I have a 17 year old daughter who receives an allowance for doing chores. With a busy teacher schedule and someone who usually doesn't carry any cash, it was difficult to get her money to her when she earned it.  Enter Greenlight. For $4.99/mo, I can add money to her card whenever I want. Furthermore, I can choose *where* she's able to spend it. While we haven't used it, there is also an additional Save and Give feature that allows your child to learn how to budget their money that includes saving it and gifting it (tithing, charity, Pay It Forward, etc.)  Recently, Greenlight has added an "Earn" feature where parents can list chores and rewards for chores completed. I've set it up to where my daughter gets a bi-weekly allowance, automatically,.To ensure I have enough money in my Parent Wallet, I've also set up for an auto-draft from my bank to add funds to my wallet on the first of every month so that money is available. However, I can add money to my Parent Wallet at any time (or add money directly to her account from my bank account).
